The paper focuses on developing a high-performing VQA system that can provide integrated textual and visual explanations, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of deep neural networks, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The evaluation of the approach involves both automatic and human evaluation metrics, which suggests that it may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
